{"lemma":"بَرِّيٌّ","slug":"بَرِّيٌّ","root":"ب.ر.ر","root_slug":"ب-ر-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ر-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2148","n2149","n2165","n2422","n2428","n2432"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%91%D9%8A%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"wild"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"overland, land, terrestrial"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"بَرّ (barr, “land”) + ـِيّ (-iyy)."},"ipa":["/bar.riː/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2148","headword_ar":"بُرَّى","root":"br","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A good, sweet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasant, word"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expression"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ benevolent and solicitous regard or treatment or conduct. ” (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n2149","headword_ar":"بَرِّىٌّ","root":"br","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belonging to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relating to, the land"},{"kind":"text","text":"as opposed to the sea or a great river. ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belonging to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relating to, the desert"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waste; growing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"living,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"produced, in the desert"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waste; wild,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in an uncultivated state."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b3-  And hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN bar~iy~apN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ بَرِّيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Uncultivated land; without seed-produce, and unfruitful; without green herbs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plants and without waters; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyfiy~apN","text_ar":"رِيفِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, M, K. *) And, simply, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~ay~apN","text_ar":"بَرَّيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~iytN","text_ar":"بَرِّيتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A'Obeyd, IAar, Sh, S, K,) the latter a variation of the former, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"being made quiescent, and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"therefore being changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiforiytN","text_ar":"عِفْرِيتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiforiyapN","text_ar":"عِفْرِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) a rel. n. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~N","text_ar":"بَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sh, T, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A desert; a waste; a spacious tract of ground without herbage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHoraA='u","text_ar":"صَحْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, A, Msb, K:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~N","text_ar":"بَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tract nearer to the desert"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albar~","text_ar":"البَرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"than it is to water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, T:) [but some write the latter word ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~iytN","text_ar":"بِرِّيتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~iytu","text_ar":"بِرِّيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brt","text_ar":"برت"},{"kind":"text","text":",) of the same measure as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sik~iytN","text_ar":"سِكِّيتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K in that art.,) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flat, even,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"level, land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a barren, flat, even,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"level, land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"bir~iytu A^aroDK baEodahaA bir~iytu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A barren, flat land, after which is a"},{"kind":"text","text":"second"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"barren, flat land"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T:) ISd says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~iytN","text_ar":"بِرِّيتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a poem of Ru-beh, [from which the ex. given above is probably taken,] is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEoliytN","text_ar":"فِعْلِيتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albar~u","text_ar":"البَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and that art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brt","text_ar":"برت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not the place in which it should be mentioned: (TA:) Lth says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albar~iytu","text_ar":"البَرِّيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a noun derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albar~iy~apu","text_ar":"البَرِّيَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"becoming quiescent, and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"becoming an inseparable"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":", as though it were a radical letter, as in the case of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiforiyapN","text_ar":"عِفْرِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which thus becomes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiforiytN","text_ar":"عِفْرِيتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"br~y~p","text_ar":"برّيّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraAriY~u","text_ar":"بَرَارِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"br~yt","text_ar":"برّيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraAriytu","text_ar":"بَرَارِيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Msb","K","Sh","T","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n2165","headword_ar":"بَرِيَ","root":"brA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. generally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buro'N","text_ar":"بُرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA='apN","text_ar":"بَرَا=ءَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of, or from, a thing; in the manners which will be explained below: (Bd ii. 51:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, in a state of freedom"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"immunity, secure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"safe."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariy^a mina AlmaraDi","text_ar":"بَرِيَ مِنَ المَرَضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA^a","text_ar":"بَرَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baruw^a","text_ar":"بَرُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buro'N","text_ar":"بُرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariy^a mn AlmrD","text_ar":"بَرِيَ من المرض"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buro'N","text_ar":"بُرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm; and the people of El-Hijáz say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA^a","text_ar":"بَرَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baro'N","text_ar":"بَرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h: (S:) accord. to As,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariYa mn","text_ar":"بَرِىَ من"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmrD","text_ar":"المرض"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the dial. of Temeem; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA^a","text_ar":"بَرَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the dial. of the people of El-Hijáz: or, accord. to AZ, the people of El-Hijáz say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA^a","text_ar":"بَرَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the rest of the Arabs say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariy^a","text_ar":"بَرِيَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA^a","text_ar":"بَرَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[alone], said of a sick man, aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariy^a","text_ar":"بَرِيَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baruw^a","text_ar":"بَرُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baro'N","text_ar":"بَرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[probably a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buro'N","text_ar":"بُرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruw^N","text_ar":"بُرُوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, accord. to Lh, the people of El- Hijáz say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA^a","text_ar":"بَرَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buro'N","text_ar":"بُرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruw^N","text_ar":"بُرُوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwo'N","text_ar":"بُرُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and the people of El-'Áliyeh, ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA^a","text_ar":"بَرَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buro'N","text_ar":"بُرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruw^u","text_ar":"بُرُوُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and Temeem,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariy^a","text_ar":"بَرِيَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buro'N","text_ar":"بُرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruw^N","text_ar":"بُرُوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA^a","text_ar":"بَرَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) said by IKtt to be the most chaste form, (TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) agreeably with analogy, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) said by Zj to be the only instance of a verb of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEala","text_ar":"فَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"for its last radical letter having its aor. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yafoEulu","text_ar":"يَفْعُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [though others mention also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraA^a","text_ar":"قَرَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqoruw^u","text_ar":"يَقْرُوُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hanaA^a","text_ar":"هَنَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yahonuw^u","text_ar":"يَهْنُوُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and asserted to be a bad form, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buro'N","text_ar":"بُرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwo'N","text_ar":"بُرُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baruw^a","text_ar":"بَرُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) not a chaste form, (TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariy^a","text_ar":"بَرِيَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) a chaste form, (TA,) [and the most common of all,] aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baro'N","text_ar":"بَرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruw^N","text_ar":"بُرُوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buro'N","text_ar":"بُرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (CK,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwo'N","text_ar":"بُرُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became free from the disease, sickness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"malady:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he recovered from it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became convalescent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"healthy, at the close of disease, but was yet weak; or he recovered, but not completely, his health and strength;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niqaha","text_ar":"نِقَهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he acquired that slight degree of soundness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"health, which comes at the close of disease, but with disease remaining in him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariy^a","text_ar":"بَرِيَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljuroju","text_ar":"الجُرْجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA^a","text_ar":"بَرَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wound healed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became in a healing state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"of frequent occurrence.] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariy^a mina AlA^amori","text_ar":"بَرِيَ مِنَ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [the only form of the verb used in this case, and in the other cases in which it is mentioned below,] aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", the latter extr., (M, K,) or rather it is very strange, for IKoot says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEima","text_ar":"نَعِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanoEumu","text_ar":"يَنْعُمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDila","text_ar":"فَضِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yafoDulu","text_ar":"يَفْضُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", are the only instances of this kind, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA='apN","text_ar":"بَرَا=ءَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA='N","text_ar":"بَرَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruw^N","text_ar":"بُرُوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buro'N","text_ar":"بُرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwo'N","text_ar":"بُرُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (CK;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbr~A^","text_ar":"تبرّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * M, K, Mgh; *) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, free from the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit, thereof; clear of having"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of having had"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taken, any part therein; guiltless of it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"irresponsible for it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in an ex. q. v. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaADN","text_ar":"عِضَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] said in relation to [a fault or the like, and] a debt, and a claim, and religion [&c.]. (Lh, M.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariy^a mina AlEayobi","text_ar":"بَرِيَ مِنَ العَيْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuyuwbi","text_ar":"العُيُوبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA='apN","text_ar":"بَرَا=ءَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, free"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the fault, defect, imperfection, blemish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vice"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Mgh, Msb,) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faults,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariy^a mina Ald~ayoni","text_ar":"بَرِيَ مِنَ الدَّيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~uyuwni","text_ar":"الدُّيُونِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA='apN","text_ar":"بَرَا=ءَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit, of the debt;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"debts;"},{"kind":"text","text":"S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"irresponsible for it"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a state of immunity with respect to it"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exempt from the demand thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bary^a","text_ar":"بَريَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayoka mino Haq~ika","text_ar":"اـِلَيْكَ مِنْ حَقِّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA='apN","text_ar":"بَرَا=ءَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA='N","text_ar":"بَرَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, M) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruw^N","text_ar":"بُرُوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit, to thee, of thy claim,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exempt from the demand thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbr~A^","text_ar":"تبرّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariy^otu A_ilayoka mino fulaAnK","text_ar":"بَرِيْتُ اـِلَيْكَ مِنْ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA='pN","text_ar":"بَرَا=ءةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have become, clear, to thee, of having"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of having had"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taken, any part with such a one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"irresponsible to thee for such a one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (AZ, T, S: * [in one copy of the S, I find the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariy^otu minoka","text_ar":"بَرِيْتُ مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", commencing the art.; but not in other copies:]) this is the only form of the verb used in this case, and in relation to debt [and the like]. (AZ, T.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He removed himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kept, far,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aloof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[from unclean things, or things occasioning blame; followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with which it may be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he shunned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avoided;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanaz~ahu","text_ar":"تَنَزَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaAEada","text_ar":"تَبَاعَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T.) [You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariy^a mina","text_ar":"بَرِيَ مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aqo*aAri","text_ar":"الاَقْذَارِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He removed himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kept, far,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aloof, from unclean things."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He manifested an excuse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asserted himself to be clear"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"irresponsible,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbr~A^","text_ar":"تبرّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and gave warning;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEo*ara","text_ar":"اَعْذَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano*ara","text_ar":"اَنْذَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T.) Hence, in the Kur [ix. 1],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA='apN mina A@ll~`hi warasuwlihi","text_ar":"بَرَا=ءَةٌ مِنَ ا@للّٰهِ وَرَسُولِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A manifestation of excuse, and a warning, from God and his apostle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA^a A@ll~`hu Alxaloqa","text_ar":"بَرَاَ ا@للّٰهُ الخَلْقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, T, S, M, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxaliyaqapa","text_ar":"الخَلِيَقَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, &c.,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baro'N","text_ar":"بَرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwo'N","text_ar":"بُرُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, Lh, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God created mankind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the beings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"things, that are created,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqa","text_ar":"خَلَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, T, M, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after no similitude,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"model,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but,"},{"kind":"text","text":"properly, though not always meaning so,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"out of pre-existing matter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] Bd says [in ii. 51] that the primary meaning of the root"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"br'","text_ar":"برء"},{"kind":"text","text":"is to denote a thing's becoming clear, or free, of, or from, another thing; either by being released [therefrom], as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariy^a AlmariyDu","text_ar":"بَرِيَ المَرِيضُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino maraDihi","text_ar":"مِنْ مَرَضِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almadoyuwnu mino daynihi","text_ar":"المَدْيُونُ مِنْ دَينِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[both sufficiently explained above]; or by production [therefrom], as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA^a A@ll~`hu A=dama mina AlT~iyni","text_ar":"بَرَاَ ا@للّٰهُ ا=دَمَ مِنَ الطِّينِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God produced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"created, Adam, from,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"out of, clay"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) This verb relates to substances [as in the exs. given above] and to accidents; and hence, [in the Kur lvii. 22,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino qboli A^ano naboraA^ahaA","text_ar":"مِنْ قبْلِ اَنْ نَبْرَاَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Before our creating it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"if"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hA","text_ar":"ها"},{"kind":"text","text":"refer to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSiybap","text_ar":"مُصِيبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", preceding it; but, as Bd says, it may refer to this, or to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroD","text_ar":"الاَرْض"},{"kind":"text","text":", or to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anofus","text_ar":"اَنْفُس"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M:) but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albaro'u","text_ar":"البَرْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has a more particular application than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxaloqu","text_ar":"الخَلْقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the former being particularly applied to the creation of animate beings, with few exceptions: you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA^a A@ll~`hu Aln~asamapa","text_ar":"بَرَاَ ا@للّٰهُ النَّسَمَةَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa xalaqa Als~am`waAti waAlA^aroDa","text_ar":"وَ خَلَقَ السَّمٰوَاتِ وَالاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God created,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"produced, man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the soul, and He created the heavens and the earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [To this verb, or perhaps to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baray","text_ar":"بَرَي"},{"kind":"text","text":", or to both,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"בָּרָ","text_ar":"בָּרָ","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the Hebrew equivalent, properly (though not necessarily always) signifying “ he created out of pre-existing matter, ” or “ he fashioned. ”]"}],"source_refs":["T","Msb","S","M","K","TA","CK","Lh","Mgh","Fr","AZ"]},{"entry_id":"n2422","headword_ar":"بَرَى","root":"brY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, K,) first pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barayotu","text_ar":"بَرَيْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baroYN","text_ar":"بَرْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He formed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fashioned, by cutting; shaped out;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pared;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T, M, K;) a reed for writing, (Lth, As, ISk, T, S, M, Msb,) and a stick, or piece of wood, (Lth, T, M,) and an arrow, (M, K,) &c.; (M;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AbtrY","text_ar":"ابترى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barawotu","text_ar":"بَرَوْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lth, T,) is a dial. var., (Msb,) used by some, who say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huma yaqoluw Albur~a","text_ar":"هُمَ يَقْلُو البُرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqoliY","text_ar":"يَقْلِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Lth, T.) ―         -b2-  And hence, (As, T,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (As, T, M, K,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fatigued,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jaded, and made to lose flesh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, * T, * S,) a she-camel, (As, T,) or a camel: (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(journeying)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered"},{"kind":"text","text":"him"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emaciated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) and in like manner one says of a year of dearth or drought. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barayotu sanaAmahaA bisayoriY EalayohaA","text_ar":"بَرَيْتُ سَنَامَهَا بِسَيْرِى عَلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I wasted her hump by my journeying upon her"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: occurring in a poem of El-Aashà. (M.)       -A2-  See also 3: ―         -b2-  and see 5, in two places."}],"source_refs":["T","M","K","S","Msb","Lth","As","ISk"]},{"entry_id":"n2428","headword_ar":"بَرًى","root":"brY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barFA","text_ar":"بَرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brw","text_ar":"برو"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n2432","headword_ar":"بَرِىٌّ","root":"brY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to an arrow,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maboriY~N","text_ar":"مَبْرِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Formed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fashioned, by cutting; shaped out;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pared"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (T, M, K;) or (M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"completely;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but not feathered, nor headed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for an arrow when first cut is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiToEN","text_ar":"قِطْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; then it is formed, or fashioned, by cutting, or shaped out, or pared, and is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariY~N","text_ar":"بَرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and when straightened, and fit to be feathered and headed, it is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qidoH","text_ar":"قِدْح"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and when feathered and headed, it becomes a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sahom","text_ar":"سَهْم"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T.)       -A2-  It is also sometimes used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariYo'N","text_ar":"بَرِىْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Kz, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brA^","text_ar":"برا"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["M","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A8%D8%B1%D9%8A/","headword_ar":"بري","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_12","lexicon_en":"Al-Muṭarrizī, al-Mughrib fī Tartīb al-Muʿrib (d. 1213 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المغرب في ترتيب المعرب للمُطَرِّزي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=17395#f0e66f","body_html":"(ب ر ي) : (الْبَوَارِي) جَمْعُ بَارِيٍّ وَهُوَ الْحَصِيرُ وَيُقَالُ لَهُ الْبُورِيَاءُ بِالْفَارِسِيَّةِ."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_51","lexicon_en":"Habib Anthony Salmone, An Advanced Learner's Arabic-English Dictionary (1889)","lexicon_ar":"حبيب سالمون، قاموس عربي انجليزي متقدم للمتعلمين","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=17395#6698ef","body_html":"بري<br> بَرَى(n. ac. بَرْي)<br>a. Planed, shaved; pared; mended (pen).<br> b. Fatigued, jaded.<br> <br> بَاْرَيَa. Vied, emulated, competed with.<br> <br> تَبَاْرَيَa. see III <br> إِنْبَرَيَa. Was smoothed, cut, mended (pen).<br> b. [La], Opposed; presented himself. <br> إِبْتَرَيَa. see I (a)<br> بَاْرِيa. Creator.<br> <br> بُرَاْيَةa. Clippings, parings; chips, shavings.<br> <br> مِبْرَاء مِبْرَاة<br> a. Penknife."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_9","lexicon_en":"Al-Zamakhsharī, Asās al-Balāgha (d. 1143 CE)","lexicon_ar":"أساس البلاغة للزمخشري","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=17395#fd6abe","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">ب ر ي</span><br><br><span>ما عندي قلم بري أي مبري، وأرفع براية القلم. قال المتنخل:</span><br><br><span>وصراء البراية عود نبيع </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> كوقف العاج عاتكة اللياط</span><br><br><span>وبفيه البري وحمىً خيبرا، وشر ما يرى.</span><br><br><span>ومن المجاز: بريت الناقة بالسير، وبرآها السفر، وناقة ذات براية: بها بقية بعد بري السفر إياها. وإنك لذو براية: لمن فيه بقية بعد السفر. وفلان يباري الريح جوداً، وأعطته الدنيا برتها إذا تمكن منها وحظي بها.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_17","lexicon_en":"Al-Fayyūmī, Al-Miṣbāḥ al-Munīr fī Gharīb al-Sharḥ al-Kabīr (d. 1368 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المصباح المنير للفيّومي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=17395#57347a","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">ب ر ي</span><span> : الْبُرَةُ مَحْذُوفَةُ اللَّامِ هِيَ حَلْقَةٌ تُجْعَلُ فِي أَنْفِ الْبَعِيرِ تَكُونُ مِنْ صُفْرٍ وَنَحْوِهِ وَالْخِشَاشُ مِنْ خَشَبٍ وَالْخِزَامَةُ مِنْ شَعْرٍ وَالْجَمْعُ</span><br><span>بُرُونَ عَلَى غَيْرِ قِيَاسٍ وَأَبْرَيْتُ الْبَعِيرِ بِالْأَلِفِ جَعَلْتُ لَهُ بُرَّةً وَبَرَيْتُ الْقَلَمَ بَرْيًا مِنْ بَابِ رَمَى فَهُوَ مَبْرِيُّ وَبَرَوْتُهُ لُغَةٌ وَاسْمُ الْفِعْلِ الْبِرَايَةُ بِالْكَسْرِ وَهَذِهِ الْعِبَارَةُ فِيهَا تَسَامُحٌ لِأَنَّهُمْ قَالُوا لَا يُسَمَّى قَلَمًا إلَّا بَعْدَ الْبِرَايَةِ وَقَبْلَهَا يُسَمَّى قَصَبَةً فَكَيْفَ يُقَالُ لِلْمَبْرِيِّ بَرَيْتُهُ لَكِنَّهُ سُمِّيَ بِاسْمِ مَا يَئُولُ إلَيْهِ مَجَازًا مِثْلُ: عَصَرْتُ الْخَمْرَ.</span><br><br><span>وَبَرِئَ زَيْدٌ مِنْ دَيْنِهِ يَبْرَأُ مَهْمُوزٌ مِنْ بَابِ تَعِبَ بَرَاءَةً سَقَطَ عَنْهُ طَلَبُهُ فَهُوَ بَرِيءٌ وَبَارِئٌ وَبَرَاءٌ بِالْفَتْحِ وَالْمَدِّ وَأَبْرَأْتُهُ مِنْهُ وَبَرَّأْتُهُ مِنْ الْعَيْبِ بِالتَّشْدِيدِ جَعَلْتُهُ بَرِيئًا مِنْهُ وَبَرِئَ مِنْهُ مِثْلُ: سَلِمَ وَزْنًا وَمَعْنًى فَهُوَ بَرِيءٌ أَيْضًا.</span><br><br><span>وَبَرَأَ اللَّهُ تَعَالَى الْخَلِيقَةَ يَبْرَؤُهَا بِفَتْحَتَيْنِ خَلَقَهَا فَهُوَ الْبَارِئُ وَالْبَرِيَّةُ فَعِيلَةٌ بِمَعْنَى مَفْعُولَةٍ.</span><br><br><span>وَبَرَأَ مَنْ الْمَرَضِ يَبْرَأُ مِنْ بَابَيْ نَفَعَ وَتَعِبَ وَبَرُؤَ بُرْءًا مِنْ بَابِ قَرُبَ لُغَةٌ.</span><br><br><span>وَاسْتَبْرَأْتُ الْمَرْأَةَ طَلَبْتُ بَرَاءَتهَا مِنْ الْحَبَلِ قَالَ الزَّمَخْشَرِيُّ اسْتَبْرَأْتُ الشَّيْءَ طَلَبْتُ آخِرَهُ لِقَطْعِ الشُّبْهَةِ.</span><br><br><span>وَاسْتَبْرَأَ مِنْ الْبَوْلِ الْأَصْلُ اسْتَبْرَأَ ذَكَرَهُ مِنْ بَقِيَّةِ بَوْلِهِ بِالنَّتْرِ وَالتَّحْرِيكِ حَتَّى يَعْلَمَ أَنَّهُ لَمْ يَبْقَ فِيهِ شَيْءٌ وَاسْتَبْرَأْتُ مِنْ الْبَوْلِ تَنَزَّهْت عَنْهُ.</span><br><br><span>وَالْبَرَى مِثْلُ: الْعَصَا التُّرَابُ وَبَارَيْتُهُ عَارَضْتُهُ فَأَتَيْتُ بِمِثْلِ فِعْلِهِ وَالْبَارِيَّةُ الْحَصِيرُ الْخَشِنُ وَهُوَ الْمَشْهُورُ فِي الِاسْتِعْمَالِ وَهِيَ فِي تَقْدِيرِ فَاعُولَةٍ وَفِيهَا لُغَاتٌ إثْبَاتُ الْهَاءِ وَحَذْفُهَا وَالْبَارِيَاءُ عَلَى فَاعِلَاءَ مُخَفَّفٌ مَمْدُودٌ وَهَذِهِ تُؤَنَّثُ فَيُقَالُ هِيَ الْبَارِيَاءُ كَمَا يُقَالُ هِيَ الْبَارِيَةُ بِوُجُودِ عَلَامَةِ التَّأْنِيثِ وَأَمَّا مَعَ حَذْفِ الْعَلَامَةِ فَمُذَكَّرٌ فَيُقَالُ هُوَ الْبَارِي وَقَالَ الْمُطَرِّزِي الْبَارِي الْحَصِيرُ وَيُقَالُ لَهُ بِالْفَارِسِيَّةِ الْبُورِيَاءُ. </span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_8","lexicon_en":"Ibn Sīda al-Mursī, Al-Muḥkam wa-l-Muḥīṭ al-Aʿẓam (d. 1066 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المحكم والمحيط الأعظم لابن سيده الأندلسي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=17395#051d52","body_html":"<span>[ب ر ي] بَرَى العُودَ والقَلَمَ والقِدْحَ وغَيْرَها بَرْيًا نَحَتَه وابْتَرَاه كبَرَاه قالَ طَرَفَةُ</span><br><br><span>(مِنْ خُطوبٍ حَدَثَتْ أَمْثالُها </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> تَبْتَرِي عُوَدَ القَوِيِّ المُسْتَمِرْ)</span><br><br><span>وقد انْبَرَى وسَهْمٌ بَرِيٌّ مَبْرِيٌّ وقِيلَ هو الكامِلُ البَرْيِ والبَرّاءَةُ والمِبْراةُ السِّكِّينُ يُبْرَى بها القَوْسُ عن أَبِي حَنِيفَةَ والبُراءُ النُّحاتَةُ قالَ أبو كَبِيرٍ</span><br><br><span>(ذَهَبَتْ بشَاشَتُه وأَصْبَحَ واضِحًا </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> حَرِقَ المَفارِق كالبُراءِ الأَعْفَرِ) </span><span>والُرايَةُ كالبُراءِ قالَ ابنُ جِنِّي هَمْزَةُ البُراءِ من الياءِ لقَوْلِهم في تأْنِيثِه البُرايَةُ وقَد كانَ قِياسُه إِذْ كانَ لَهُ مُذكَّرٌ أن يُهْمَزَ في حالِ تأنِيثِه فيُقالُ بُراءَةٌ أَلا تَراهُم لما جاءُوا بواحِدِ العَظَاءِ والعَباءِ عَلَى تذكِيرِه قالُوا عَظَاءَةٌ وعَباءَةٌ فهَمَزُوا لما بَنَوا المُؤَنَّثَ على مُذَكَّرِه وقد جاءَ نَحْوَ البُراءِ والبُرايَةِ غَيْرُ شيءٍ قالوا الشَّقاءُ والشَّقاوَةُ ولم يَقُولُوا الشَّقاءَةُ وقالُوا ناوِيَةٌ بَيِّنَةَ النَّواءِ والنَّوايَة ولم يَقُولوا النَّواءَة وكَذلك الرَّجاءُ والرَّجاوَةُ وفي هَذا ونَحْوِه دَلالةٌ على أَنَّ ضَرْبًا من المُؤَنَّثِ يُرْتَحَلُ غَيْرَ مُحْتَذًى به نَظِيرُه من المُذكَّرِ فجَرَت البُرايَةُ مَجْرَى التَّرْقُوَةِ وما لا نَظِيرَ له من المُذَكَّرِ في لَفْظٍ ولا وَزْنٍ وهُوَ من بُرايَتِهِم أي خُشارَتِهم وناقَةٌ ذاتُ بُرايَةٍ أي شَحْمٍ ولَحْمٍ وقِيلَ ذاتُ بُرايَةٍ أي بَقاءٍ على السَّيْرِ وبَعَيرٌ ذُو بُرايَةٍ أي باقٍ على السَّيْرِ فقَط قالَ اللِّحْيانِيُّ وقالَ بَعْضُهم بُرايَتُهُما بَقِيَّةُ بُدْنِهِما وقُوَّتهما وبَراهُ السَّفَرُ يَبْرِيه بَرْيًا هَزَلَه عنه أيضا قالَ الأَعْشَى</span><br><br><span>(بأَدْماءَ حُرْجُوجٍ سَنامَها </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> بسَيْرِي عَلَيْها بعدَما كانَ تامِكَا)</span><br><br><span>والبَرَى التُّرابُ يُقالُ في الدُّعاء على الإنْسانِ بفِيهِ البَرَى كما يُقالُ بفِيه التُّرابُ وفي الدعاء بفِيهِ البَرَى وحُمَّى خَبِيرًا وشَرُّ ما يُرَى فإِنَّه خَيْسَرَى لما يُؤْثِرُونَه من السَّجْعِ وقد تَقَدَّم وبَرَى له بَرْيًا وانْبَرَى عَرَضَ وبارَاهُ عارَضَهُ وتَبَرَّى مَعْرُوفَه وبمَعْرُوفِه اعْتَرَض لَه قال خَوّاتُ بنُ جُبَيْرٍ</span><br><br><span>(وأَهْلَةِ وُدٍّ قَدْ تَبَرَّيْتُ وُدَّهُم </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> وأَبْلَيْتُهُم في الحَمْدِ جُهْدِي ونائِلِي)</span><br><br><span>والبارِي والبارِياءُ الحَصِيرُ المَنْسُوج وقِيلَ الطَّرِيقُ فارسِيٌّ مُعْرّب </span><span>وبَرَى اسمُ مَوْضِع قال تأَبَّطَ شَرّا</span><br><br><span>(ولما سَمِعْتُ العُوص تَرْغُو تَنَفَّرَتْ </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> عَصافِيرُ رأْسِي من بَرًى فعَوائِنَا)</span>"}]}}